BQL Query  SELECT *
FROM STREAM(MAX, TIME)
WHERE browser-id='2siknmdd6kaqm'
WINDOWING(EVERY, 1, RECORD, FIRST, 1, RECORD)  JSON Query  {  
    filters :[  
      {  
          field : browser-id ,
          operation : == ,
          values :[  
             2siknmdd6kaqm 
         ]
      }
   ],
    aggregation :{  
       size :1,
       type : RAW ,
       fields :null,
       attributes :null
   },
    window :{  
       emit :{  
          type : RECORD ,
          every :1
      },
       include :{  
          type : RECORD ,
          first :1
      }
   },
    projection :{  
       fields :{  
          browser-id : browser-id ,
          event : event ,
          demographics.country : country 
      }
   },
    duration :9223372036854775807
}  This is a query that will capture raw data, and has a sliding window of size 1. This query will return window results immediately whenever a single record that matches the filters flows through the system. The filters in this example will only match records from a particular browser.  This query will run for the maximum amount of time that the backend is configured to allow.  Results might look like this:  records :[  
